# Optional but strongly recommended. Without it the app falls back to
# lyrics.ovh, which only searches song titles and artists — so it can only
# find songs when you happen to sing the title phrase.
#
# Genius's search hits actual lyric content, so "I was happy in the haze of
# a drunken hour" finds "Heaven Knows I'm Miserable Now" by The Smiths.
#
# Get a Client Access Token at https://genius.com/api-clients:
#   1. Sign in / create a Genius account
#   2. Click "New API Client" (any URL works for the website + redirect URI
#      fields — Genius doesn't validate them for read-only access)
#   3. Click "Generate Access Token" on the resulting page
#   4. Paste it below (no quotes)
EXPO_PUBLIC_GENIUS_TOKEN=

# Optional. If unset, the Spotify button is hidden and the app still works
# (Apple Music links and lyric matching don't need any auth).
#
# Get a Client ID from https://developer.spotify.com/dashboard
#   1. Create an app
#   2. Add http://localhost:8081/ to its redirect URIs (and your deploy URL
#      later, e.g. https://yourdomain.com/)
#   3. Copy the Client ID below — there is no secret to set, this app uses
#      Authorization Code with PKCE.
EXPO_PUBLIC_SPOTIFY_CLIENT_ID=
